The expression $|x - 2|$ represents the distance from $x$ to $2$. So 
$|x - 2| \leq 5$ means "$x$ is at most 5 units from 2."

Using the theorem:
\[
 |x - 2| \leq 5 \implies -5 \leq x - 2 \leq 5
\]

Add 2 to all three parts:
\[
 -5 + 2 \leq x \leq 5 + 2
\]
\[
 -3 \leq x \leq 7
\]

