Note that $|x + 3| = |x - (-3)|$, which represents the distance from 
$x$ to $-3$.

Using the theorem:
\[
 |x + 3| \geq 4 \implies x + 3 \leq -4 \;\text{ or }\; x + 3 \geq 4
\]

Solve each part:
$$
 x + 3 \leq -4 &\implies x \leq -7 \\
 x + 3 \geq 4 &\implies x \geq 1
$$

Solution: $x \leq -7$ or $x \geq 1$

